  <row Id="100" PostTypeId="1" AcceptedAnswerId="102" CreationDate="2015-03-10T14:30:00.000" Score="47" ViewCount="10542" Body="&lt;p&gt;From the view of somebody offering a web application, when somebody connects with TLS (https) to our service, is it safe to transmit all sensitive data over this line?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Can there still be &lt;code&gt;eavesdropping&lt;/code&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;" OwnerUserId="201" LastActivityDate="2024-01-15T09:00:00.000" Title="Does an established HTTPS connection mean a line is really secure?" Tags="&lt;cryptography&gt;&lt;ssl&gt;&lt;tls&gt;" AnswerCount="2" CommentCount="1" ContentLicense="CC BY-SA 3.0" />
